<HL> Financing Business:
Magna International Inc.</HL>
<DD> 05/07/87</DD>
<SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO>
<IN> MAGAF
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN>
<TEXT>
   MAGNA INTERNATIONAL INC. said it filed with Canadian securities commissions to offer 2.5 million class A voting shares at $29.50 (Canadian) each, or a total of about $73.8 million. 
The Toronto-based automobile parts maker said proceeds would be used to reduce bank debt. 
Lead underwriter is McLeod Young Weir Ltd. Magna International class A closed at $29.75, down 75 cents, yesterday on the Toronto Stock Exchange. 

